quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  70,40,"So, I do swear by the Lord of ˹all˺ the points of sunrise and sunset that We are truly capable"
  70,41,"of replacing them with ˹others˺ better than them, and We cannot be prevented ˹from doing so˺"
  70,42,"So let them indulge ˹in falsehood˺ and amuse ˹themselves˺ until they face their Day, which they have been threatened with—"
  70,43,"the Day they will come forth from the graves swiftly, as if racing to an idol ˹for a blessing˺"
  70,44,"with eyes downcast, utterly covered with disgrace. That is the Day they have ˹always˺ been warned of"
  71,1,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people ˹saying to him˺, “Warn your people before a painful punishment comes to them.”"
  71,2,"Noah proclaimed, “O my people! I am truly sent to you with a clear warning"
  71,3,"worship God ˹alone˺, fear Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"He will forgive your sins, and delay your end until the appointed time. Indeed, when the time set by God comes, it cannot be delayed, if only you knew!”"
  71,5,"He cried, “My Lord! I have surely called my people day and night"
  71,6,but my calls only made them run farther away
  71,7,"And whenever I invite them to be forgiven by You, they press their fingers into their ears, cover themselves with their clothes, persist ˹in denial˺, and act very arrogantly"
  71,8,Then I certainly called them openly
  71,9,then I surely preached to them publicly and privately
  71,10,"saying, ‘Seek your Lord’s forgiveness, ˹for˺ He is truly Most Forgiving"